div3.p:
For four bloody years the Confederacy stood the shock of all the power and resources of the greatest republic on the face of the globe, and fought for independence on more than one hundred battle-fields, and at last, when her armies were worn away by attrition and her means of resistance exhausted, succumbed to overwhelming numbers and resources.
Vanquished, yet victorious;
Overcome, but not humiliated;
Defeated, but not dismayed.
